main event: An unidentified flying object sighting occurred in Chicago, Illinois, on May 9, 1964, involving three objects observed for three seconds.
interesting points: The objects were seen oscillating and were compared to three moons through fog.,Witness reported exceptional clarity of the night sky and stated it was a once-a-year night.,The duration of the observation was notably brief, lasting only three seconds.,The observer initially thought the objects were not aircraft and considered them to be around third magnitude.,Multiple explanations were considered, including after-images caused by previously looking at a red light.
witness description: A civilian observer who described the objects as pulsating with a greenish tinge.
